e Department of Software Engineering offers a specialized academic environment for students interested in software design, software development processes, software testing, software architecture, and project management. The program emphasizes the complete software development life cycle, from requirements analysis and system design to implementation, quality assurance, deployment, and maintenance. The department was established to address the growing demand for skilled software professionals in industry and academia. It provides a balanced approach to learning through classroom teaching, laboratory practice, team projects, internships, seminars, and exposure to current technologies such as web development, cloud computing, data analytics, machine learning, and software quality engineering. Vision & Mission Vision To be a center of excellence in Software Engineering education, research, and innovation by developing professionals capable of creating high-quality, scalable, and cost-effective software solutions for society and industry. Mission To provide quality education in software engineering through industry-relevant curriculum and practical training. To develop strong skills in software analysis, design, development, testing, and maintenance. Develop problem-solving skills through hands-on projects and industry exposure. To encourage innovation, teamwork, research, and ethical responsibility in software development. To prepare students for successful careers, higher studies, and entrepreneurship in software-related domains. Program outcomes: Students graduating from the Department of Software Engineering are expected to: Apply engineering and computing principles to solve software development problems. Analyze user requirements and design appropriate software systems. Develop, test, and maintain software using modern programming languages, tools, and frameworks. Work effectively in teams and manage software projects within time and quality constraints. Follow professional ethics, communication standards, and best practices in software engineering. Adapt to new technologies and engage in lifelong learning. --> Curriculum Highlights A software engineering curriculum generally includes programming, data structures, algorithms, database systems, operating systems, software engineering principles, software architecture, testing, quality assurance, project management, web technologies, and cloud-related topics. The curriculum is designed to build knowledge progressively from fundamentals to advanced software engineering practices. Students study subjects such as Programming in C/C++/Java/Python, Data Structures, Database Management Systems, Operating Systems, Software Engineering, Software Testing, Software Quality and Metrics, Web Development, Cloud Computing, Agile Methods, Software Project Management, and Full Stack Development. The program also includes mini projects, internships, laboratory work, and major software projects to strengthen practical understanding. Laboratories & Facilities The department provides facilities that support software development, experimentation, and collaborative learning. Well-equipped computer laboratories. High-speed internet and smart classrooms. Software tools for AI, programming, and machine learning. Project guidance and technical support for research and innovation. Student Activities The department encourages students to take part in academic and co-curricular activities that improve technical, communication, and leadership skills. Workshops and seminars. Technical quizzes and coding competitions. Paper presentations and project exhibitions. Industrial visits and internship programs. Hackathons and innovation challenges. Research & Innovation The department promotes research and innovation in software engineering and emerging computing areas. Faculty and students are encouraged to work on applied and research-oriented problems in software quality, testing, analytics, machine learning, web applications, and intelligent systems. Research initiatives in the department aim to address practical challenges in software reliability, usability, automation, security, and scalable system development. The department supports innovation through project work, technical events, collaborative learning, and participation in research activities. Career Opportunities Software Engineering graduates are well prepared for careers in the software and IT industry because the discipline focuses on building high-quality systems within real-world constraints of time, budget, and performance. Faculty The Department of Software Engineering is supported by dedicated and qualified faculty members who bring academic knowledge, technical expertise, and mentoring support to students. Our faculty team is committed to student success through quality teaching, academic guidance, project supervision, and career mentoring. The department promotes a learner-centered environment where faculty and students work together on knowledge creation and practical problem solving. Faculty Profile Programs --> Sr. No. Name of the Staff Designation Qualifications Subjects Taught Experience Photo Contact No. Email ID 1 Dr Kale Suhas Babasaheb Assistant Professor & HoD MSc IT, SET, PhD CFD, DE, PHP, HTML, CSS, J2EE, AI/ML 25 Years 9822622964 ctekbeed@gmail.com 2 Mr. Tadgure Yashpal Tukaram Assistant Professor MSc CM SE, ST, HiberNet, Mobile Comm. 5 Years 9561696007 ytadgure@gmail.com 3 Mr Patel Riyaj Abdulajij Assistant Professor MSc CS Java, Spring Boot, C#, PHP 2.5 Years 9764292757 riyazpatel396@gmail.com 4 Mr Patil Ganesh Shivaji Assistant Professor MCA SE, OS, OA, CD, WT 4 Years 8669047511 ganeshsp7818@gmail.com SN Name of the Course Eligibility Duration 01 B.Sc. (Software Engineering) 12 th - Science Faculty 3/4 Years 02 M.Sc. (Software Engineering) B.Sc. or Any Computer Graduate 2 Years Syllabus Open Syllabus of All Courses! REV. CBCS UG COURSES (Revised CBCS) UG FY 2019-20 B.Sc (CS) - FY B.Sc (SE